PTSD Analogy — Micro-Sleep and Flashbulb Encoding
===================================================
2026-03-10

Observation
-----------
Micro-sleep's "immediate" trigger mode mirrors the mechanism behind PTSD:
information entering too fast, bypassing normal consolidation, and burning
into weights without proper integration or validation.

The Analogy
-----------
Human memory has two consolidation paths:
  1. Normal: hippocampus buffers → REM sleep integrates → cortex stores
  2. Traumatic: amygdala hijacks → flashbulb encoding → bypasses REM

The system has the same two paths:
  1. Normal: FactBuffer → full /sleep (LoRA + graduation test + PPL gate)
  2. Flashbulb: high-priority fact → micro-sleep "immediate" mode → LoRA
     fires immediately, no graduation test, no PPL validation

Risks (map to PTSD symptoms)
-----------------------------
- **Catastrophic forgetting** (intrusive memories displacing normal recall):
  Aggressive LoRA on a high-priority fact overwrites previously learned facts.
  Especially dangerous on 3B where weight space is narrow.

- **Encoding distortion** (distorted traumatic memories):
  High-priority facts get 3x training repetitions. If the extraction was wrong
  (hallucinated or misunderstood), the error gets burned deep. Harder to
  un-learn than a normal-priority fact.

- **Silent PPL degradation** (general cognitive impairment):
  Multiple micro-sleep passes without a full sleep cycle's PPL gate can
  quietly degrade general coherence. No one checks the damage until
  the next full sleep.

Existing Safeguards
-------------------
- Cooldown timer (120s between micro-sleeps in immediate mode)
- Minimum age before training (60s)
- Max 3 facts per pass
- "cycle" mode (default): batches facts, waits for 90-min ultradian rhythm
  — the healthy consolidation analog

The Full Sleep Fix
------------------
Full /sleep is the equivalent of healthy REM processing:
  - Trains on ALL facts (not just high-priority)
  - Graduation test: verifies each fact was properly encoded
  - PPL gate: checks nothing got corrupted
  - Retreat mechanism: un-graduates facts that fail recall

Micro-sleep without full sleep = encoding without integration.

Design Implication
------------------
The "cycle" mode exists specifically to prevent the PTSD analog. It imposes
a biological rhythm (90-min BRAC) that batches consolidation, preventing
any single fact from hijacking the training pipeline. The "immediate" mode
should be reserved for genuinely critical corrections (the user says
"actually, that's wrong") where the cost of delayed encoding exceeds the
risk of interference.
